1
00:00:01,002 --> 00:00:02,461
[ mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,545 --> 00:00:03,879
[ penguins wenk ]

3
00:00:06,132 --> 00:00:07,466
[ all cheering ]

4
00:00:10,303 --> 00:00:11,470
[ screeches ]

5
00:00:13,389 --> 00:00:14,432
D> Adventure Time )

6
00:00:14,515 --> 00:00:16,058
» Come on, grab your friends »

7
00:00:16,142 --> 00:00:18,561
» We'll go to very distant lands J

8
00:00:18,644 --> 00:00:20,896
» With Jake the dog
and Finn the human

9
00:00:20,980 --> 00:00:22,732
D The fun will never end >

10
00:00:22,815 --> 00:00:24,900
D It's Adventure Time »

11
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:33,993
[ birds chirping ]

12
00:00:34,076 --> 00:00:36,495
[ munch! munch! munch! ]

13
00:00:36,579 --> 00:00:37,872
Aaah!

14
00:00:39,582 --> 00:00:42,084
[ sluuuuurp! ]

15
00:00:42,168 --> 00:00:46,172
[ munching loudly ]

16
00:00:50,051 --> 00:00:53,054
[ sighing ]

17
00:00:56,182 --> 00:00:58,059
Hey, Jake.
What's wrong?

18
00:00:58,142 --> 00:01:00,311
You look dumpy.
How come?

19
00:01:00,394 --> 00:01:04,148
I-Is it because
of that metal box?

20
00:01:04,231 --> 00:01:05,775
Is something sad inside?

21
00:01:05,858 --> 00:01:07,777
No. It's nothing.

22
00:01:07,860 --> 00:01:10,029
There's lots of boxes
that have nothing in them.

23
00:01:10,112 --> 00:01:12,198
But also, you could put
something in the box.

24
00:01:12,281 --> 00:01:13,783
And then it won't be empty!

25
00:01:13,866 --> 00:01:15,493
Does that make you feel better?

26
00:01:15,576 --> 00:01:16,911
[ chuckles ]

27
00:01:16,994 --> 00:01:18,662
You're a charmer,
Finn human.

28
00:01:18,746 --> 00:01:20,873
No.
It's...well...

29
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:22,792
Lady Rainicorn doesn't want to play

30
00:01:22,875 --> 00:01:25,002
the game Card Wars with me.

31
00:01:26,879 --> 00:01:28,339
| always beat her.

32
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:30,800
So she says, "no more
card warring."

33
00:01:30,883 --> 00:01:32,343
What's Card Wars?

34
00:01:32,426 --> 00:01:33,677
It's a fantasy card game

35
00:01:33,761 --> 00:01:35,930
that's super-complicated and awesome,

36
00:01:36,013 --> 00:01:38,140
but, well...
oh, it's kinda stupid.

37
00:01:38,224 --> 00:01:39,767
Never mind.

38
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:41,435
How come you never
talked about it before?

39
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:43,270
It sounds cool.
- Really?!

40
00:01:43,354 --> 00:01:45,439
Well, | thought you'd say
it was for nerds

41
00:01:45,523 --> 00:01:47,066
who do not know how life is

42
00:01:47,149 --> 00:01:48,943
outside of the nerd universe.

43
00:01:49,026 --> 00:01:50,277
I-It is, man.

44
00:01:50,361 --> 00:01:52,405
But | still totally
want to play it.

45
00:01:52,488 --> 00:01:53,823
So no more moping, okay?

46
00:01:53,906 --> 00:01:55,699
Thanks, Finn.

47
00:01:58,744 --> 00:02:01,497
[ window creaks, glass shatters ]

48
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:06,377
Oh, hey, Beemo.
You want to play, too?

49
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:10,297
No! | do not play
such games... with Jake!

50
00:02:10,381 --> 00:02:12,425
- What's that mean?
- JAKE: Ah, whatever.

51
00:02:12,508 --> 00:02:15,386
Let's play the game!

52
00:02:15,469 --> 00:02:17,596
So, what kind of stakes
do we play for?

53
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:19,557
How about the loser...

54
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,225
is a dweeb,

55
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:22,852
and the winner is a cool guy?

56
00:02:22,935 --> 00:02:24,520
Those are good stakes.

57
00:02:30,568 --> 00:02:32,194
Coffee grounds, beetle butter,

58
00:02:32,278 --> 00:02:34,822
grape jelly, kimchi,

59
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:37,992
aaand this stuff.

60
00:02:38,075 --> 00:02:40,744
Hey! You're ruining that pop
with weird taste!

61
00:02:40,828 --> 00:02:44,081
[ squiggle! squiggle! ]

62
00:02:44,165 --> 00:02:46,500
We drink when the game is over.

63
00:02:46,584 --> 00:02:47,793
Oh, gross.

64
00:02:47,877 --> 00:02:50,254
Now, let me explain the rules.

65
00:02:51,255 --> 00:02:52,882
That's basically the basics.

66
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:55,009
So once we have
our kingdom set up...

67
00:02:55,092 --> 00:02:56,135
[ electronic beeping ]

68
00:02:56,218 --> 00:02:57,636
...it's time to start to play...

69
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:59,555
for the gloryyyy!

70
00:02:59,638 --> 00:03:01,182
Huh?

71
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:02,558
Hey, were you asleep?

72
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:04,894
I'll have to explain it
all over again!

73
00:03:04,977 --> 00:03:06,687
Doesn't matter.
Let's just play.

74
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:08,522
But if you don't know the rules,

75
00:03:08,606 --> 00:03:10,524
then you're gonna lose
in the first couple rounds,

76
00:03:10,608 --> 00:03:12,234
like Lady always does.

77
00:03:12,318 --> 00:03:14,695
And then you'll hate the game.
And then you'll hate me/

78
00:03:14,778 --> 00:03:16,238
And then, and then --

79
00:03:16,322 --> 00:03:18,032
Pfft!
You think you're gonna win?

80
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:21,368
I'm gonna crush you --
party-dance style, dweeb!

81
00:03:21,452 --> 00:03:23,204
[ laughs triumphantly ]
Bring it!

82
00:03:23,287 --> 00:03:25,206
So, how do | get
my land on the map?

83
00:03:25,289 --> 00:03:26,832
Oh.

84
00:03:26,916 --> 00:03:29,293
You, uh, floop your land cards.

85
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:31,086
[ electronic beeping ]

86
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:33,589
Uh...

87
00:03:33,672 --> 00:03:35,174
Keep those honeys hidden,

88
00:03:35,257 --> 00:03:37,134
or I'll get a strategic advantage!

89
00:03:37,218 --> 00:03:38,802
Oh!

Hmm...

90
00:03:38,886 --> 00:03:40,679
Okay, | go first.

91
00:03:40,763 --> 00:03:43,557
| floop the Silo of Truth!

92
00:03:43,641 --> 00:03:45,226
[ whirring ]

93
00:03:45,309 --> 00:03:47,019
[ gasps ]
Hey!

94
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:49,021
Pfft!
You got really lame cards.

95
00:03:49,104 --> 00:03:50,064
Hmm...

96
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:53,067
I'll take the Cerebral Blood
Storm, though.

97
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:54,527
[ whirs ]

98
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:55,819
Huh?

99
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:57,821
Okay, now it's the battle phase.

100
00:03:57,905 --> 00:04:01,325
I'm attacking your schoolhouse
with my Husker Knights.

101
00:04:01,408 --> 00:04:02,618
[ horse snorts ]

102
00:04:02,701 --> 00:04:06,705
And, I'm casting Cerebral Blood Storm.

103
00:04:06,789 --> 00:04:07,915
[ shimmer! ]

104
00:04:07,998 --> 00:04:11,418
So, what do you use to defend?

105
00:04:11,502 --> 00:04:13,295
[ horse whinnies ]

106
00:04:13,379 --> 00:04:15,756
Uh...
can my Cool Dog

107
00:04:15,839 --> 00:04:17,758
and Ancient Scholar
defeat your Husker Knights?

108
00:04:17,841 --> 00:04:19,468
[ laughs ]

109
00:04:19,552 --> 00:04:21,136
Of course not!

110
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:23,973
Hmm.
Then | floop the pig...

111
00:04:24,056 --> 00:04:25,558
What?!
[ laughs ]

112
00:04:25,641 --> 00:04:27,726
- What?
- Okay, okay.

113
00:04:27,810 --> 00:04:31,564
First of all, you don't floop
a creature to make it fight.

114
00:04:31,647 --> 00:04:33,274
You activate a creature.

115
00:04:33,357 --> 00:04:34,900
Hmm. No!

116
00:04:34,984 --> 00:04:37,987
It says | can
floop the pig. See?

117
00:04:38,070 --> 00:04:42,324
[ pig snorting ]

118
00:04:42,408 --> 00:04:44,326
[ gasps ]
No!

119
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:46,203
He's eating all my cornfields!

120
00:04:46,287 --> 00:04:49,456
My Husker Knights
draw energy from corn!

121
00:04:49,540 --> 00:04:51,542
And since I'm not
actually attacking,

122
00:04:51,625 --> 00:04:53,419
your Cerebral Blood Storm
only does damage

123
00:04:53,502 --> 00:04:55,546
to your own kingdom's troops.

124
00:04:55,629 --> 00:04:56,463
[ thunder crashes ]

125
00:04:56,547 --> 00:04:57,798
[ gasps ]

126
00:04:57,881 --> 00:05:00,801
You just wiped out
my entire attack!

127
00:05:00,884 --> 00:05:03,721
What do you expect if all your
power units come from corn?

128
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:06,724
Pigs eat corn, dude.
Cornfields stink.

129
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:09,184
Cornfields are awesome!

130
00:05:09,268 --> 00:05:11,895
What makes you think you know
so much about Card Wars?!

131
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:14,607
- It's just logic.
- Your turn.

132
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:15,774
Hmm...

133
00:05:15,858 --> 00:05:17,526
You're supposed
to discard a card

134
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:19,361
and pick up a new one first.

135
00:05:19,445 --> 00:05:20,529
Oh, right.

136
00:05:20,613 --> 00:05:22,823
Look at you.
You're a babe in the woods.

137
00:05:22,906 --> 00:05:24,950
Your beginner's luck
ends this round!

138
00:05:25,034 --> 00:05:27,119
Hmm.

139
00:05:30,456 --> 00:05:33,626
Spirit Tower!
And the Cave of Solitude?!

140
00:05:33,709 --> 00:05:35,794
Now my battle phase
begins.

141
00:05:35,878 --> 00:05:39,798
| activate my ancient scholar
to begin studying.

142
00:05:39,882 --> 00:05:42,635
And | also move my pig
to the Cave of Solitude

143
00:05:42,718 --> 00:05:44,887
so he can take a nap.

144
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:47,681
That's it?
You're not attacking?

145
00:05:47,765 --> 00:05:49,391
I'll attack on a different turn.

146
00:05:49,475 --> 00:05:51,393
Ha!
Then the seas have aligned

147
00:05:51,477 --> 00:05:53,395
and the five winds
waft the smell of victory

148
00:05:53,479 --> 00:05:55,272
to my palace doors!

149
00:05:55,356 --> 00:05:57,399
| cast
"Field of Nightmares"

150
00:05:57,483 --> 00:05:59,401
and activate my legion of ear-lings

151
00:05:59,485 --> 00:06:00,944
to scare your pig to death!

152
00:06:01,028 --> 00:06:02,029
HlLa, la, la, lad

153
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:03,947
My pig's in the Cave of Solitude.

154
00:06:04,031 --> 00:06:06,283
Um...
| cast "Teleport"

155
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:08,035
to move your
pig to the empty field

156
00:06:08,118 --> 00:06:09,620
so | can attack him!

157
00:06:09,703 --> 00:06:11,622
Uh... wouldn't "Teleport"
only work

158
00:06:11,705 --> 00:06:13,916
on your own creatures?
- You're right.

159
00:06:13,999 --> 00:06:15,709
I'm gonna slay that pig, though.

160
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:18,462
How? You don't have any
creatures that can touch him.

161
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:19,588
Ugh!

162
00:06:19,672 --> 00:06:22,549
Face it, man.
I'm the cool guy.

163
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:23,842
Hmm...

164
00:06:23,926 --> 00:06:26,470
[ gasps ]
You're the cool guy, huh?

165
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:29,431
Well, let me make it a little
hot for you, then.

166
00:06:29,515 --> 00:06:31,100
[ chuckles ]

167
00:06:31,183 --> 00:06:33,102
| floop the volcano.

168
00:06:33,185 --> 00:06:34,103
What?!

169
00:06:34,186 --> 00:06:35,979
That'll destroy your kingdom,
too, won't it?!

170
00:06:36,063 --> 00:06:37,981
Hmph! Maybe.
Oh!

171
00:06:38,065 --> 00:06:39,858
Aah!

172
00:06:39,942 --> 00:06:40,943
My pig!

173
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:42,069
dla, lad

174
00:06:42,152 --> 00:06:44,279
Aah!

175
00:06:44,363 --> 00:06:46,532
[ chuckles evilly ]

176
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:48,450
The pig is dead.

177
00:06:48,534 --> 00:06:50,327
Now | reconstitute my cornfields

178
00:06:50,411 --> 00:06:53,122
using the "Reclaim Landscape" spell.

179
00:06:53,205 --> 00:06:54,707
My Husker Knights, revive!

180
00:06:54,790 --> 00:06:55,916
[ horse snorts ]

181
00:06:55,999 --> 00:06:58,877
And [ still have
my battle phase.

182
00:06:58,961 --> 00:07:03,424
Hiding in the useless swamp,
the Immortal Maize Walker!

183
00:07:03,507 --> 00:07:05,634
| love corn!

184
00:07:05,718 --> 00:07:07,636
Ah!

185
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:10,889
Cornfields give the immortal
maize walker triple damage.

186
00:07:10,973 --> 00:07:12,266
Uh...

187
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:14,727
| told you cornfields
are awesome!

188
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:16,645
Your Ancient Scholar
and Cool Dog

189
00:07:16,729 --> 00:07:18,480
won't survive this time.

190
00:07:18,564 --> 00:07:20,482
Actually, my Ancient
Scholar's been studying

191
00:07:20,566 --> 00:07:22,151
the "Raise the Dead" ability.

192
00:07:22,234 --> 00:07:24,069
- So what?
- So...

193
00:07:24,153 --> 00:07:26,697
My Ancient Scholar
raises the dead.

194
00:07:26,780 --> 00:07:28,031
[ pig snorts ]

195
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:29,366
| floop the pig.

196
00:07:29,450 --> 00:07:33,120
No-0-0-0-0-0!

197
00:07:33,203 --> 00:07:36,039
Look.
My tower's doing a thing.

198
00:07:36,123 --> 00:07:39,501
Hominy-hominy-hominy!

199
00:07:39,585 --> 00:07:41,795
You ganked
my Spirit Walker!

200
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:43,338
Ah!

201
00:07:43,422 --> 00:07:46,467
[ mumbling angrily ]

202
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:49,136
Uh, maybe we should
take a break?

203
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:51,305
[ groans ]

204
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:52,806
Your turn.

205
00:07:52,890 --> 00:07:54,433
Huh?

206
00:07:54,516 --> 00:07:55,517
You play!

207
00:07:55,601 --> 00:07:57,019
You play!

208
00:07:58,020 --> 00:07:59,480
Oh, zang.

209
00:07:59,563 --> 00:08:01,440
| do not play such games...

210
00:08:01,523 --> 00:08:02,858
...with Jake.

211
00:08:04,818 --> 00:08:07,154
Sorry! | gotta
use the boy style room.

212
00:08:08,739 --> 00:08:12,075
Beemo! Beemo!

213
00:08:12,159 --> 00:08:13,410
Beemo chop!

214
00:08:13,494 --> 00:08:16,079
If this were a real attack,
you'd be dead.

215
00:08:16,163 --> 00:08:18,665
Beemo! Jake's acting
boonoonoonoos!

216
00:08:18,749 --> 00:08:21,710
Oh, no! Are you winning
the game of Card Wars?

217
00:08:21,794 --> 00:08:23,712
- Yeah!
- That's terrible!

218
00:08:23,796 --> 00:08:26,715
If Jake loses that game,
he gets super depressed!

219
00:08:26,799 --> 00:08:30,427
When | beat him, he wouldn't
talk to me for a month!

220
00:08:30,511 --> 00:08:31,887
What?!

221
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:33,889
| only played
so he wouldn't be bummed!

222
00:08:33,972 --> 00:08:36,683
Finn, you must take a dive.

223
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:38,101
Okay, I'll try.

224
00:08:38,185 --> 00:08:40,437
But I'm a Card Wars
super Amadeus.

225
00:08:40,521 --> 00:08:41,522
Whoop!

226
00:08:43,148 --> 00:08:46,610
Play... the... game.

227
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:48,612
[ thinking ]
Grob. Better make this look good.

228
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:50,364
[ breathes deeply ]

229
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:53,700
All right, Jake.
Prepare for my ultimo-attack!

230
00:08:53,784 --> 00:08:57,329
Well, I've still got
my Wandering Bald Man.

231
00:08:57,412 --> 00:08:59,122
Oh, no.

232
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:00,582
[ thinking ]
| need to get rid of my pig

233
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,626
so Jake can reconstitute
his cornfields.

234
00:09:04,503 --> 00:09:06,213
| activate the pig

235
00:09:06,296 --> 00:09:09,132
to attack your Wandering Bald Man.

236
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:11,552
That's stupid.

237
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:12,970
Just attack
with Immortal Maize Walker

238
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:14,638
and get the game over with!

239
00:09:14,721 --> 00:09:15,931
No way!

240
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:18,433
You've underestimated me
and my pig all day.

241
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,605
[ thinking ]
Please lose. Please lose.

242
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:34,283
No-0-0-0!

243
00:09:34,366 --> 00:09:36,034
[ grunts ]

244
00:09:36,118 --> 00:09:38,328
[ pig snorts ]

245
00:09:38,412 --> 00:09:41,582
[ pig squealing ]

246
00:09:41,665 --> 00:09:45,043
Oh-ho!
Oh! Oh, yeah!

247
00:09:45,127 --> 00:09:48,380
Pigs can't leave mud landscapes
once they're on them!

248
00:09:48,463 --> 00:09:51,300
Ha ha ha!
The pig is mine!

249
00:09:51,383 --> 00:09:54,094
First, I'll play Reclaim Landscape.

250
00:09:54,177 --> 00:09:56,847
Then | cast "Summon Archer Dan."

251
00:10:01,852 --> 00:10:04,563
Whoa, math...

252
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,192
[ grunts ]

253
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:10,652
M'boys!

254
00:10:10,736 --> 00:10:12,529
You have no creatures left.

255
00:10:12,613 --> 00:10:14,865
That's the game, boy!

256
00:10:14,948 --> 00:10:18,535
The five winds blow through
cornfields once again

257
00:10:18,619 --> 00:10:21,038
for the glory of Jakoria!

258
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:23,665
Heh. You got me.

259
00:10:23,749 --> 00:10:25,667
In your face!

260
00:10:25,751 --> 00:10:28,795
It's time to drink up!

261
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:31,340
JAKE:
It looks like you are the dweeb

262
00:10:31,423 --> 00:10:33,717
and /'m the cool guy.

263
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:36,053
[ slurps ]

264
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:37,804
[ sniffs ]

265
00:10:37,888 --> 00:10:39,681
[gags ]

266
00:10:39,765 --> 00:10:41,350
Is it too gross for you, man?

267
00:10:41,433 --> 00:10:42,893
No, no.

268
00:10:42,976 --> 00:10:44,686
| got to take what's coming to me.

269
00:10:44,770 --> 00:10:46,813
